                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, Dec. 30: Japans Sumitomo Corporation will raise its stake in Indian light commercial vehicle manufacturer Swaraj Mazda Ltd to 53.52 per cent from 39.49 per cent. This follows Mahindra amp; Mahindras decision to exit Swaraj Mazda by selling its 14.04 per cent stake, which it acquired after buying Punjab Tractors Ltd. The stake sale could be priced at around Rs 292 per share.                            
	 New Delhi, Dec. 30: Insurance regulator IRDA has relaxed debt and equity investment limits for insurance firms to increase flow of funds to the sector. Insurance firms can now invest up to 20 per cent of their funds in the infrastructure and housing sector with an additional 5 per cent debt investment if it is investing in one company.                            
	 Mumbai, Dec. 30: Calcutta-based Uco Bank has restructured its equity capital by reducing it by a third from the current level of around Rs 800 crore, a move that will help the bank attract more investors.                                                                                                                         
